<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Your 2FA Backup Codes - {{appName}}</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <style>
        /* Base styles */
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f9fafb;
        }

        /* Container styles */
        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #ffffff;
        }

        /* Codes container */
        .codes-container {
            background-color: #f1f5f9;
            border-radius: 5px;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            font-family: monospace;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        /* Individual code */
        .code {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #ffffff;
            border: 1px solid #cbd5e1;
            border-radius: 3px;
            padding: 8px 12px;
            margin: 5px;
            font-weight: bold;
            letter-spacing: 1px;
        }

        /* Warning box */
        .warning-box {
            background-color: #fef2f2;
            border-left: 4px solid #ef4444;
            padding: 15px;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }

        /* Responsive styles */
        @media only screen and (max-width: 600px) {
            .container {
                width: 100% !important;
            }

            .code {
                display: block;
                margin: 10px 0;
                text-align: center;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    {{> header}}

    <div class="container">
        <h2 style="color: #1f2937; margin-top: 20px;">Your 2FA Backup Codes</h2>

        <p>Hello {{name}},</p>

        <p>You have successfully enabled Two-Factor Authentication for your {{appName}} account. To ensure you always
            have access to your account, we've generated the following backup codes for you:</p>

        <div class="codes-container">
            {{#each codes}}
            <div class="code">{{this}}</div>
            {{/each}}
        </div>

        <div class="warning-box">
            <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: bold; color: #b91c1c;">Important:</p>
            <ul style="margin-top: 8px; color: #b91c1c;">
                <li>Keep these codes in a safe place. They are the only way to regain access to your account if you lose
                    your authentication device.</li>
                <li>Each code can only be used once.</li>
                <li>These codes are as important as your password - don't share them with anyone.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <p>You can generate new backup codes at any time by visiting your account security settings.</p>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin: 30px 0;">
            {{#trackButton (concat appUrl "/account/security") "Security Settings" emailId "button"}}{{/trackButton}}
        </div>

        <p>If you didn't enable 2FA on your account, please contact our support team immediately.</p>

        <p>Thanks,<br>The {{appName}} Team</p>
    </div>

    {{> footer recipient=to emailId=id}}
</body>

</html>